{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"4cHM1zjFd82I95jGZJVo5","title":"ThreePapersPhD","desc":"","updated":1642659386335,"created":1642658445444,"custom":{},"fname":"dissertation.publication.ThreePapersPhD","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"49cd63b55ebb250a62577a3adabe5255","links":[],"anchors":{"the-three-papers-phd-thesis-a-guide-for-the-perplexed":{"type":"header","text":"The 'three papers' PhD thesis: a guide for the perplexed","value":"the-three-papers-phd-thesis-a-guide-for-the-perplexed","line":8,"column":0,"depth":2},"faq":{"type":"header","text":"FAQ","value":"faq","line":31,"column":0,"depth":3}},"children":[],"parent":"4HuJK1YbDiF5JO1p0COda","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"threepapersphd\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#threepapersphd\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>ThreePapersPhD</h1>\n<h2 id=\"the-three-papers-phd-thesis-a-guide-for-the-perplexed\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#the-three-papers-phd-thesis-a-guide-for-the-perplexed\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>The 'three papers' PhD thesis: a guide for the perplexed</h2>\n<p>Athens University of Economics and Business</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.dept.aueb.gr/sites/default/files/deos/3_paper_phd_guide.pdf\">https://www.dept.aueb.gr/sites/default/files/deos/3_paper_phd_guide.pdf</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>3 separate, publishable papers</li>\n<li>normal journal article length (5000-10000 words)</li>\n<li>free-standing and independent, but on related themes</li>\n<li>normally preceded by short introduction</li>\n<li>may include lit review but not necessary</li>\n</ul>\n<ol>\n<li>Intro and background</li>\n<li>first paper</li>\n<li>second paper</li>\n<li>third paper</li>\n<li>conclusions and implications</li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li>usually 5 chapters</li>\n<li>150 A4 pages (35000 words) plus appendices, although appendices are commonly appended to each paper, rather than the thesis</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"faq\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#faq\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>FAQ</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Do papers need to be published?\n<ul>\n<li>no, they need to be publishable, although publication is <em>prima facie</em> evidence of publishability</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>co-authorship?\n<ul>\n<li>must be substantially the learner's work, so first author</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Lit review?\n<ul>\n<li>format involves jettisoning conventional ideas, such as a 'lit review' chapter</li>\n<li>each article contains a lit review, but of an appropriate length for a journal article</li>\n<li>that said, some people have included a lit review chapter</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"5jYEnrzN6hGFE8UIGFZmq","title":"Literature","desc":"","updated":1641603128996,"created":1640807033123,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"50d4df57e1d51dc7dc70adcb1107174a","links":[],"anchors":{"colin-madland":{"type":"header","text":"Colin Madland","value":"colin-madland","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1},"lookup":{"type":"header","text":"Lookup","value":"lookup","line":10,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["B7myY49HkkF7myZxUuBxl","L22lROYOyWkZEdDIPsTID","yTIqwRe5IPrxiJ01mdsxI","LoO5XTqa9xfDY8xhh161H","jADP0D1g2XDXGy7YK6hfq","VpmPuvmeSOhFST1BB6QTT"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"# Colin Madland\n\nUsing this site to build a networked literature repository\n## Lookup\n\nThis section contains useful links to related resources.\n\n- [Getting Started Guide](https://link.dendron.so/6b25)\n- [Discord](https://link.dendron.so/6b23)\n- [Home Page](https://wiki.dendron.so/)\n- [Github](https://link.dendron.so/6b24)\n- [Developer Docs](https://docs.dendron.so/)\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":4,"useFMTitle":true,"useNoteTitleF